Write the cross method in the Vector3D class.
Remember to respond with a snippet in the form of the following:
```
class Vector3D {
    cross(otherVector) {
        // your code here
    }
}
```

```javascript
class Vector3D {
    cross(otherVector) {
        const x = this.y * otherVector.getZ() - this.z * otherVector.getY();
        const y = this.z * otherVector.getX() - this.x * otherVector.getZ();
        const z = this.x * otherVector.getY() - this.y * otherVector.getX();
        return new Vector3D(x, y, z);
    }
}
```
